QuestionText: What is the average speed of the car if it travels 250 miles in 4 hours and 30 minutes?
If a bakery sells 250 loaves of bread at $2 each and 100 loaves at $3 each, what is the total revenue?
A car travels from City A to City B at an average speed of 60 km/h and returns at an average speed of 40 km/h. What is the average speed for the entire trip?
If a person invests $1000 at a 5% annual interest rate, how much will they have after 2 years?
A survey found that 75% of respondents prefer coffee and 25% prefer tea. If 200 people were surveyed, how many prefer tea?
A water tank can hold 1000 liters of water. If 300 liters of water are already in the tank, what percentage of the tank is filled?
A company has 500 employees and each employee produces 20 units of product per day. If the company operates 5 days a week, how many units of product are produced per week?
A student scored 85, 90, and 78 on three tests. What is their average score?
A car rental company charges $40 per day plus $0.25 per mile. If a customer rents a car for 3 days and drives 200 miles, what is the total cost?
A group of friends want to split a bill evenly. If the bill is $120 and there are 8 friends, how much will each friend pay?
